<br>
 <br>
Any Master Potter with at least kindly faction in Thurgadin can create a personal transport potion to the city of the Coldain Dwarves in Velious. This project requires items that are purchased from vendors in Thurgadin and looted from mobs found in Crystal Caverns, a dungeon in the Eastern Wastes, the zone just east of the Great Divide where Thurgadin is located. <br>
 <br>
<br>
 <br>
The entrance to Crystal Caverns is found near the center of the Eastern Wastes, inside the walls of the Orc Camp. At the back of the camp you will find a small gated, walled in courtyard containing a crystal. Touch the crystal to enter the dungeon. The loc of the entrance crystal is -4000, 475. <br>
<br>
 <br>
The Thurgadin Gate potion is trivial at pottery level 127. Both a potter’s wheel and a kiln, needed for this project, can be found in the Thurgadin Bank. <br>
You must first make a Velium Vial. To do this, place three separate pieces of crystalline silk, two glass shards, and a SMALL BRICK of Velium in a pottery wheel. The bricks and silks can both be found in Crystal Caverns. The bricks are looted off miners and the silk off the spiders at the bottom. <br>
<br>
Fire the resulting vial in a kiln along with one high quality firing sheet. The glass shards and high quality firing sheets can be purchased from a vendor in the Thurgadin Bank named Gilthan Brittleblade. He’s located in the stall farthest away from the door of the bank.<br>
<br>
With the resulting vial, go out the door of the Thurgadin Bank, turn right and go the second merchant house on the left. (It’s located down in the church area.) There you will find Frundle Frenkler. She will not respond if hailed, however, if you say, &quot;What velium vapors,&quot; (and your faction is at least &quot;warmly&quot;) she will give you a Velium Purifier, which is a container. So be sure to have an OPEN primary inventory slot.<br>
 <br>
<br>
 <br>
In the Purifier provided by Frundle Frenkler, place the Velium Vile and two separate pieces of &quot;a small chunk of Velium.&quot; These are also found in the Crystal Caverns and are looted off the orc miners there. Combine these three items, and you will have a Thurgadin Gate Potion! <br>
Although the completed potion is lore/nodrop, the components are not. So you can make as many of the Velium Vials as you want. Right now, I have five empty vials in the bank. Each time I use a potion, I just make another.<br>
<br>
For excellent information on pottery, as well as all the trade skills, go to www.eqtraders.com. You can find out there how to increase your trade skills the fastest and cheapest way.<br>
 <br>
